did.abstract: The Philip C. Keenan Papers contain correspondence and subject files on spectral classification and MIRA variables. Philip Keenan was a professor of astronomy at the Ohio State University.

bioghist.head: Biographical Note
bioghist.p: Philip Childs Keenan (1908-2000) was a professor of astronomy at the Ohio State University from 1946 to 1976. He, along with co-author W.W. Morgan, developed the M-K Standard of stellar spectral classification in an atlas published in 1943.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The Philip C. Keenan Papers contain correspondence and subject files on spectral classification and MIRA variables.
